    "body": "Made with code, align with deepgemm validation solution.\r\n\r\n## Summary\r\nAdd a diffusion NVFP4 scaled-mm correctness test under `python/sglang/jit_kernel/tests/diffusion/`.\r\n\r\nThe test covers:\r\n- checkpoint-side NVFP4 weight padding and scale-interleave processing\r\n- FLUX.2 representative shape correctness for both `jit_cutlass` and `flashinfer2`\r\n- DeepGEMM-style numeric comparison via `calc_diff = 1 - 2<x,y> / (||x||^2 + ||y||^2)` with the FP4 threshold aligned to DeepGEMM\r\n\r\nThis keeps the test colocated with the diffusion JIT kernel tests while registering it to a B200 CI suite so the NVFP4 path runs on Blackwell instead of being skipped on H100-only kernel runners.\r\n",
    "created_at": "2026-04-05T00:13:21Z",
